# Runtime data rules

These rules apply when editing the `.maestro/` control-plane domains outside `.maestro/engine/`.

## Memory citation (R-001, R-002)

- Every memory entry inferred from source code must include `confidence` and `source` (file path).
- Every memory entry from `inputs/` must include `source: "inputs/<relative-path>"`.
- Conflicts between code and inputs/ are recorded in `.maestro/knowledge/project.yaml.conflicts[]`.

## Task artifact contract (R-012)

- Task folder: `.maestro/work/tasks/TASK-YYYYMMDD-NNN-slug/`
- Required baseline depends on mode: none for direct, task/progress/verification for assisted, and
  the full task-analysis pipeline for governed.
- Implementation/QC artifacts created only by matching workflow phase.
- Canonical Dev→QC handoff: `.maestro/work/tasks/<task_id>/qc-handoff.md`. Do not duplicate elsewhere.

## Bug routing (R-009)

- Blocker bugs: `.maestro/work/bugs/blockers/<bug-id>.yaml` — stops QC immediately.
- Non-blocker bugs: `.maestro/work/bugs/non-blockers/<bug-id>.yaml` — QC continues on unaffected cases.
- Every bug must include reproduction steps, expected vs actual, impacted services.

## Secret rules (R-013)

- Never write real secrets, passwords, raw tokens, private keys, session cookies, or long logs into `.maestro/` artifacts.
- Redact sensitive values before persisting bug/QC/memory/handoff artifacts.

## Workflow state

- `.maestro/runtime/workflow-state.yaml` is mutated only by Coordinator.
- Every state transition records `updated_at`, `updated_by`, `reason`.

## Model, activity, and response UI

- `.maestro/config/model-routing.yaml` controls agent-to-model profile routing.
- `.maestro/runtime/agent-activity.yaml` backs `/status` activity, elapsed/ETA, token, and cost reporting.
- `.maestro/config/response-ui.yaml` controls markdown/text response layout modes; it does not control native Cursor UI chrome.
- Do not record exact ETA values unless the tool exposes reliable metrics.
